WEBVTT

00:03.003 --> 00:05.210
<i>(eerie music)</i>

00:05.297 --> 00:07.834
<i>(male presenter, off)
THERE IS A FIFTH DIMENSION</i>

00:07.925 --> 00:10.838
<i>BEYOND THAT
WHICH IS KNOWN TO MAN.</i>

00:10.928 --> 00:13.386
<i>IT IS A DIMENSION
AS VAST AS SPACE</i>

00:13.472 --> 00:16.213
<i>AND AS TIMELESS AS INFINITY.</i>

00:16.308 --> 00:19.767
<i>IT IS THE MIDDLE GROUND
BETWEEN LIGHT AND SHADOW.</i>

00:19.853 --> 00:22.515
<i>BETWEEN SCIENCE
AND SUPERSTITION.</i>

00:22.606 --> 00:25.849
<i>AND IT LIES
BETWEEN THE PIT OF MAN'S FEARS</i>

00:25.943 --> 00:28.025
<i>AND THE SUMMIT
OF HIS KNOWLEDGE.</i>

00:28.111 --> 00:31.024
<i>THIS IS THE DIMENSION
OF IMAGINATION.</i>

00:31.114 --> 00:33.367
<i>IT IS AN AREA WHICH WE CALL</i>

00:33.450 --> 00:37.318
<i>THE TWILIGHT ZONE.</i>

00:46.129 --> 00:48.166
[car braking
and engine revving]

01:01.228 --> 01:02.138
[horn blaring]

01:05.732 --> 01:07.564
[horn blaring]

01:09.278 --> 01:11.110
[horn blaring]

01:11.196 --> 01:12.857
WHEN YOU'RE
FINISHED, MISTER.

01:12.948 --> 01:14.404
HOW ABOUT
SOME SERVICE?

01:14.491 --> 01:16.073
WHEN IT'S QUIET.

01:16.159 --> 01:18.241
[sighs]
I'M SORRY.

01:18.328 --> 01:20.820
FILL IT UP,
WILL YOU?

01:20.914 --> 01:24.032
SURE.

01:24.126 --> 01:26.914
<i>(male presenter, off)
MARTIN SLOAN, AGE 36.</i>

01:27.004 --> 01:32.590
<i>OCCUPATION, VICE PRESIDENT,
AD AGENCY, IN CHARGE OF MEDIA.</i>

01:32.634 --> 01:36.093
<i>THIS IS NOT JUST A SUNDAY
DRIVE FOR MARTIN SLOAN</i>

01:36.179 --> 01:40.013
<i>HE PERHAPS DOESN'T KNOW IT AT
THE TIME, BUT IT'S AN EXODUS.</i>

01:40.100 --> 01:45.220
<i>SOMEWHERE UP THE ROAD,
HE'S LOOKING FOR SANITY</i>

01:45.314 --> 01:49.103
<i>AND SOMEWHERE UP THE ROAD
HE'LL FIND SOMETHING ELSE.</i>

01:55.198 --> 01:57.815
OIL CHANGE AND LUBE JOB.
THAT WHAT YOU WANT?

01:57.909 --> 01:58.944
YEAH.

01:59.036 --> 02:00.401
TAKE ABOUT AN HOUR.

02:00.495 --> 02:03.988
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'M IN NO HURRY.

02:04.082 --> 02:08.417
THAT'S HOMEWOOD
UP AHEAD, ISN'T IT?

02:08.502 --> 02:10.756
YEP. ABOUT A MILE
AND A HALF.

02:10.839 --> 02:12.500
I USED TO LIVE
IN HOMEWOOD.

02:12.591 --> 02:14.298
GREW UP THERE,
AS A MATTER OF FACT.

02:14.384 --> 02:16.466
HAVEN'T BEEN BACK
IN 20, 25 YEARS.

02:16.553 --> 02:19.671
20, 25 YEARS.

02:19.765 --> 02:21.881
YESTERDAY I JUST GOT
IN THE CAR AND DROVE.

02:21.975 --> 02:23.932
I HAD TO GET OUT
OF NEW YORK CITY.

02:24.019 --> 02:28.559
ONE MORE BOARD MEETING
PHONE CALL, REPORT, PROBLEM

02:28.649 --> 02:33.394
I WOULD HAVE JUMPED
RIGHT OUT THE WINDOW.

02:33.487 --> 02:35.569
THAT'S WALKING DISTANCE,
ISN'T IT?

02:35.656 --> 02:38.148
YEAH. ABOUT A
MILE AND A HALF.

02:38.241 --> 02:40.323
YEAH, THAT'S
WALKING DISTANCE.

03:14.444 --> 03:16.355
YEAH? WHAT'LL IT BE?

03:18.990 --> 03:21.072
I DON'T SUPPOSE
YOU STILL MAKE

03:21.159 --> 03:23.992
THOSE GREAT CHOCOLATE SODAS, DO YOU?
THREE SCOOPS?

03:24.079 --> 03:25.740
HOW'S THAT?

03:25.831 --> 03:28.869
WELL, I SPENT HALF MY LIFE
IN THIS DRUGSTORE.

03:28.959 --> 03:30.620
GREW UP HERE.

03:30.711 --> 03:32.668
ONE THING I ALWAYS
REMEMBER ORDERING

03:32.754 --> 03:34.916
WAS A CHOCOLATE SODA
WITH THREE SCOOPS.

03:35.006 --> 03:36.917
IT WAS ONLY A DIME!

03:44.307 --> 03:46.719
YOU LOOK FAMILIAR TO ME.

03:46.810 --> 03:49.051
HAVE I SEEN YOU BEFORE?

03:49.146 --> 03:51.478
I GOT THAT KIND OF FACE.

03:51.565 --> 03:53.181
OH.

03:53.275 --> 03:57.064
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME,
20 YEARS TO BE EXACT.

03:57.112 --> 03:58.978
WISH I HAD A BUCK

03:59.072 --> 04:01.609
FOR EVERY HOUR
I SAT AT THIS FOUNTAIN--

04:01.700 --> 04:05.409
GRAMMAR SCHOOL RIGHT
THROUGH THIRD YEAR HIGH.

04:05.495 --> 04:08.453
TOWN LOOKS THE SAME TOO.

04:08.540 --> 04:10.030
PRETTY AMAZING, YOU KNOW?

04:10.125 --> 04:12.742
<i>20 YEARS TO LOOK
SO EXACTLY THE SAME.</i>

04:12.836 --> 04:14.326
THAT'LL BE A DIME.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.411
A DIME? THREE SCOOPS?

04:16.505 --> 04:18.213
THAT'S THE WAY
WE MAKE 'EM.

04:18.300 --> 04:20.666
WELL, YOU'RE GOING
TO LOSE YOUR SHIRT THAT WAY.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.672
NOBODY SELLS SODAS
FOR A DIME ANYMORE.

04:22.763 --> 04:24.424
THEY DON'T?

04:24.514 --> 04:25.595
WHERE YOU FROM?

04:25.682 --> 04:27.593
<i>NEW YORK.</i>

04:29.936 --> 04:31.597
MMM.

04:31.688 --> 04:33.645
THAT'S A GOOD SODA.

04:33.732 --> 04:34.938
<i>TASTE OKA Y?</i>

04:35.025 --> 04:36.106
MMM, WONDERFUL.

04:36.193 --> 04:38.104
YOU KNOW, IT'S FUNNY

04:38.195 --> 04:41.108
HOW MANY MEMORIES
YOU CONNECT WITH A PLACE.

04:41.198 --> 04:43.189
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
IF I EVER CAME BACK HERE

04:43.283 --> 04:45.115
EVERYTHING WOULD BE
ALL CHANGED.

04:45.202 --> 04:48.945
YOU KNOW,
NOTHING RECOGNIZABLE.

04:49.039 --> 04:51.872
INSTEAD, IT'S JUST AS IF,

04:51.958 --> 04:54.746
JUST AS IF
I'D LEFT YESTERDAY.

04:57.589 --> 05:02.129
JUST AS IF
I'D BEEN AWAY OVERNIGHT.

05:02.219 --> 05:05.462
I ALMOST EXPECT MR. VVILSON TO
BE IN THE STOCKROOM SLEEPING

05:05.555 --> 05:07.592
<i>JUST LIKE HE ALWAYS DID
BEFORE HE DIED.</i>

05:11.311 --> 05:12.972
IT'S ONE
OF THE MEMORIES I HAVE

05:13.063 --> 05:14.519
OLD MAN WILSON--

05:14.606 --> 05:16.392
MAY GOD REST HIS SOUL.

05:16.483 --> 05:18.394
SLEEPING IN HIS BIG
COMFORTABLE CHAIR

05:18.485 --> 05:19.850
IN THE OTHER ROOM.

05:19.945 --> 05:21.481
WELL,

05:21.571 --> 05:23.312
HERE YOU ARE.

05:23.406 --> 05:24.567
THANKS A LOT.

05:26.243 --> 05:27.404
THAT'S A BUCK.

05:27.494 --> 05:28.655
<i>YEAH.</i>

05:28.745 --> 05:30.827
IT WAS WORTH IT.

05:30.914 --> 05:33.326
SO LONG!

05:33.416 --> 05:37.626
<i>[suspense music]</i>

05:58.525 --> 06:00.266
(clears throat)

06:00.360 --> 06:01.862
MR. WILSON?

06:03.488 --> 06:05.525
YEP, CHARLIE?

06:05.615 --> 06:09.779
VVE'RE GOING TO NEED SOME MORE
CHOCOLATE SYRUP, MR. VVILSON.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.783
I'LL ORDER SOME MORE
OF IT THIS AFTERNOON.

06:17.252 --> 06:19.243
<i>[suspense music
and dogs barking]</i>

06:23.133 --> 06:27.593
PAUL COX, MICHAEL BRADBURY

06:34.311 --> 06:38.896
VAN BUREN, BRUNI.

06:41.401 --> 06:42.766
<i>(little boy)
HI.</i>

06:42.861 --> 06:44.317
<i>HI.</i>

06:44.404 --> 06:45.735
HI.

06:48.950 --> 06:50.065
<i>PRETTY GOOD.</i>

06:50.118 --> 06:52.109
MAGGIE'S NOT BAD.

06:55.123 --> 06:59.082
[sighs] I USED TO PLAY MARBLES. WE
USED TO GIVE THEM SPECIAL NAMES.

06:59.169 --> 07:03.914
THE STEELE KIND
WE CALLED THOSE "STEELIES",

07:03.965 --> 07:08.004
THE CLEAR KIND THAT YOU COULD SEE
THROUGH VVE CALLED THOSE "CLEARIES".

07:08.094 --> 07:09.835
YOU STILL GIVE
THEM SPECIAL NAMES?

07:09.930 --> 07:11.512
SURE.

07:11.598 --> 07:14.511
I USED TO PLAY HIDE
AND SEEK OVER THERE.

07:14.601 --> 07:17.013
VVE'D ALL CIRCLE AROUND
THE OLD MAN'S BACK

07:17.103 --> 07:18.355
AND WE USED TO PUNCH IT.

07:18.438 --> 07:20.679
SEE THAT HOUSE?

07:20.774 --> 07:23.687
RIGHT ACROSS THE STREET?
I USED TO LIVE THERE.

07:23.777 --> 07:25.984
SLOAN HOUSE?

07:26.071 --> 07:27.277
YOU STILL
CALL IT THAT?

07:27.322 --> 07:29.438
STILL CALL IT WHAT?

07:29.532 --> 07:31.193
SLOAN HOUSE.

07:31.284 --> 07:35.278
MY NAME IS SLOAN. MARTIN SLOAN.
VVHAT'S YOURS?

07:35.372 --> 07:38.956
YOU'RE NOT MARTY SLOAN. I KNOVV
MARTY SLOAN AND YOU'RE NOT HIM!

07:39.042 --> 07:42.455
OH, I'M NOT?
WELL, LET'S JUST SEE.

07:42.504 --> 07:45.166
WHAT THE DRIVER'S
LICENSE SAYS. HUH?

08:03.733 --> 08:06.441
<i>(woman) BOBBY, COME DOWN FROM THERE.
BOBBY!</i>

08:06.528 --> 08:08.235
<i>BOBBY, LISTEN TO ME.</i>

08:08.321 --> 08:09.652
BOBBY?

08:09.739 --> 08:11.321
BOBBY, MIND ME.

08:11.408 --> 08:13.240
<i>WILL YOU COME DOWN
FROM THAT TREE?</i>

08:13.326 --> 08:14.532
COME ON, BOBBY.

08:14.619 --> 08:15.859
<i>BOBBY, LISTEN TO ME.</i>

08:15.954 --> 08:17.240
COME ON, GET DOWN.

08:17.330 --> 08:18.365
<i>BOBBY!</i>

08:18.456 --> 08:20.538
THAT'S A BOY.

08:20.625 --> 08:22.081
COME ON. RIGHT HERE.

08:22.168 --> 08:24.785
WHAT AM I EVER
GOING TO DO WITH YOU?

08:24.879 --> 08:26.836
AH, IT'S WONDERFUL,
ISN'T IT?

08:26.923 --> 08:28.004
THE PARK?

08:28.091 --> 08:29.081
CERTAINLY IS.

08:29.175 --> 08:31.086
ALL RIGHT, BOBBY.

08:31.177 --> 08:33.168
THAT'S PART OF SUMMER, TOO.

08:33.221 --> 08:36.339
MUSIC FROM THE MERRY-GO-ROUND,
THE CALLIOPE.

08:36.433 --> 08:39.721
AND THE COTTON CANDY,
THE ICE CREAM,

08:39.811 --> 08:41.677
AND THE BAND CONCERT.

08:41.730 --> 08:43.846
NOTHING QUITE
AS GOOD EVER.

08:43.940 --> 08:46.898
NOTHING QUITE AS GOOD
AS SUMMER AND BEING A KID.

08:46.985 --> 08:48.771
ARE YOU FROM
AROUND HERE?

08:48.862 --> 08:52.196
NO. OH, WHAT I MEAN IS I
USED TO BE A LONG TIME AGO.

08:52.240 --> 08:53.947
LIVED A COUPLE BLOCKS AWAY.

08:54.034 --> 08:56.696
I PLAYED BASEBALL
ON THAT FIELD OVER THERE

08:56.786 --> 09:00.199
AND THAT MERRY-GO-ROUND--
OH, MY GOODNESS.

09:00.248 --> 09:02.285
I GREW UP
WITH THAT MERRY-GO-ROUND.

09:02.375 --> 09:06.869
I CARVED MY NAME ON THAT POST
ON THE BANDSTAND ONE SUMMER.

09:06.963 --> 09:10.752
I WAS 11 YEARS OLD
AND I CARVED MY--

09:29.903 --> 09:31.769
<i>(Martin)
MARTIN SLOAN.</i>

09:33.156 --> 09:35.488
YOU'RE MARTIN SLOAN?

09:35.575 --> 09:38.738
YES, SIR, BUT I
DIDN'T MEAN NOTHING. HONEST.

09:38.828 --> 09:40.990
<i>LOTS OF KIDS
CARVE THEIR NAME HERE.</i>

09:41.081 --> 09:42.321
<i>NO KIDDING.</i>

09:42.415 --> 09:43.917
<i>I'M NOT THE FIRST.</i>

09:44.000 --> 09:46.116
YOU ARE MARTIN SLOAN.

09:46.211 --> 09:47.827
OF COURSE YOU ARE.

09:47.921 --> 09:49.411
<i>THAT'S THE WAY I LOOKED.</i>

09:49.464 --> 09:50.545
<i>[suspense music]</i>

09:50.632 --> 09:52.714
MARTIN!

09:52.801 --> 09:54.257
MARTIN!

09:54.302 --> 09:56.919
MARTIN!

10:23.289 --> 10:24.575
[rings doorbell]

10:28.962 --> 10:30.043
YES?

10:32.132 --> 10:33.964
YES? WHOM DO YOU
WANT TO SEE?

10:34.050 --> 10:36.667
POP.

10:36.761 --> 10:39.344
<i>Woman:
WHO IS IT, ROBERT?</i>

10:39.430 --> 10:40.807
MOM.

10:40.849 --> 10:42.055
IS THAT MOM?

10:42.142 --> 10:43.678
WHO ARE YOU?

10:43.768 --> 10:45.145
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

10:45.228 --> 10:46.639
WHO IS IT?

10:46.729 --> 10:48.891
YOU'RE BOTH HERE.

10:48.982 --> 10:51.064
HOW CAN
YOU BE HERE?

10:51.151 --> 10:53.483
WHAT DO YOU WANT,
YOUNG MAN?

10:53.570 --> 10:56.904
MOM, DON'T YOU KNOW ME?

10:56.990 --> 10:58.355
I'M MARTIN!

10:58.449 --> 10:59.826
MARTIN?

10:59.868 --> 11:01.450
MUST BE A LUNATIC
OR SOMETHING.

11:01.536 --> 11:03.322
YOU MUSTN'T BE FRIGHTENED.

11:03.413 --> 11:06.030
I GREVV UP HERE, MOM. DON'T
YOU KNOVV YOUR OVVN SON?

11:08.835 --> 11:10.121
[bangs door]

11:26.728 --> 11:28.560
<i>(young man)
HI.</i>

11:28.646 --> 11:31.604
LIKE IT?

11:38.114 --> 11:39.946
IT'S GOT A RUMBLE SEAT.

11:40.033 --> 11:43.025
IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME SINCE
I'VE SEEN A RUMBLE SEAT.

11:43.119 --> 11:45.201
WHERE YOU BEEN,
MISTER? SIBERIA?

11:45.288 --> 11:47.029
POP JUST BOUGHT ME THIS.

11:47.123 --> 11:49.865
FIRST BRAND-NEW CAR
I'VE EVER OWNED.

11:49.959 --> 11:52.075
THIS? BRAND-NEW?

11:52.170 --> 11:54.662
FIRST OF ITS KIND
IN THE WHOLE TOWN.

11:54.756 --> 11:57.965
<i>RIGHT OUT OF DETROIT
YESTERDAY MORNING.</i>

12:03.973 --> 12:07.557
BRAND NEW?
34 ROADSTER?

12:07.602 --> 12:10.594
RIGHT OUT OF DETROIT?

12:10.688 --> 12:12.554
BRAND NEW?

12:12.649 --> 12:15.437
<i>[music intensifies]</i>

12:26.412 --> 12:29.154
<i>[distant bell tolling]</i>

12:29.249 --> 12:32.332
<i>(male presenter, offl A MA N
OA N THINK A LOT OF THOUGHTS</i>

12:32.418 --> 12:35.831
<i>AND WALKA LOT OF PAVEMENTS
BETWEEN AFTERNOON AND NIGHT,</i>

12:35.922 --> 12:38.289
<i>AND TO A MAN
LIKE MARTIN SLOAN,</i>

12:38.383 --> 12:41.501
<i>TO WHOM MEMORY
HAS SUDDENLY BECOME REALITY,</i>

12:41.594 --> 12:45.132
<i>A RESOLVE CAN COME JUST
AS CLEARLY AND INEXORABLY</i>

12:45.223 --> 12:47.635
<i>AS STARS IN THE SUMMER NIGHT.</i>

12:47.725 --> 12:50.467
<i>MARTIN SLOAN
IS NOW BACK IN TOWN</i>

12:50.561 --> 12:55.977
<i>AND HIS RESOLVE IS TO PUT
A CLAIM TO HIS PAST.</i>

13:26.514 --> 13:28.130
BACK AGAIN, HUH?

13:28.182 --> 13:29.684
<i>I HAD TO COME
BACK, POP.</i>

13:29.767 --> 13:33.476
THIS IS MY HOUSE
AND THIS IS MY GLOVE.

13:33.563 --> 13:36.225
YOU GAVE IT TO ME
ON MY 11th BIRTHDAY.

13:36.316 --> 13:38.978
<i>AND THE BASEBALL
AUTOGRAPHED BY LOU GEHRIG.</i>

13:39.068 --> 13:41.184
WHO ARE YOU?

13:41.279 --> 13:42.360
WHAT DO YOU WANT HERE?

13:42.447 --> 13:44.063
I DON'T KNOW.

13:44.157 --> 13:46.865
I JUST WANT TO REST.
I WANT TO STOP RUNNING.

13:46.951 --> 13:48.533
L-- I BELONG HERE.

13:48.619 --> 13:50.747
DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?
I BELONG HERE.

13:50.830 --> 13:52.537
NOW, LOOK,
YOU'RE PROBABLY SICK.

13:52.623 --> 13:54.034
YOU'RE HAVING
DELUSIONS.

13:54.125 --> 13:55.707
I DON'T WANT TO HURT YOU.

13:55.793 --> 13:58.000
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO GET INTO TROUBLE.

13:58.046 --> 14:02.005
BUT IF YOU HANG AROUND HERE,
THERE MAY BE TROUBLE.

14:02.050 --> 14:03.757
<i>(woman)
ROBERT?</i>

14:03.843 --> 14:05.504
<i>(woman) WHO WERE YOU TALKING TO?</i>

14:05.595 --> 14:07.506
MOM! LOOK AT ME.

14:07.597 --> 14:10.259
YOU HAVE A SON NAMED
MARTIN, HAVEN'T YOU?

14:10.350 --> 14:12.057
HE GOES TO EMERSON
PUBLIC SCHOOL.

14:12.143 --> 14:13.725
IN THE MONTH
OF AUGUST HE SPENDS

14:13.811 --> 14:15.427
AT HIS AUNT'S FARM
NEAR BUFFALO.

14:15.521 --> 14:16.807
A COUPLE OF SUMMERS

14:16.898 --> 14:18.480
YOU'VE GONE
TO SARATOGA LAKE,

14:18.566 --> 14:20.102
RENTED A COTTAGE THERE.

14:20.193 --> 14:22.275
ONCE I HAD A SISTER.

14:22.362 --> 14:24.524
SHE DIED WHEN SHE
WAS A YEAR OLD.

14:24.614 --> 14:25.695
WHERE IS MARTIN?

14:25.782 --> 14:27.022
I'M MARTIN!

14:27.116 --> 14:28.572
YOU'VE GOT
TO BELIEVE ME.

14:28.659 --> 14:31.071
I'M MARTIN.
YOU'VE GOT TO BELIEVE ME!

14:31.162 --> 14:32.948
LOOK, HERE ARE
MY IDENTIFICATION,

14:33.039 --> 14:34.279
ALL MY CARDS.

14:34.374 --> 14:35.864
THEY'LL TELL YOU
WHO I AM.

14:35.958 --> 14:37.869
LOOK AT THEM. GO ON,
THEY'LL TELL YOU.

14:44.509 --> 14:47.297
<i>[distant merry
go round music]</i>

14:50.973 --> 14:53.681
MARTIN.

14:53.768 --> 14:56.100
MARTIN, I'VE GOT
TO TALK TO YOU.

14:56.187 --> 14:58.178
MARTIN.

15:07.115 --> 15:09.777
MARTIN!

15:09.867 --> 15:11.073
<i>MARTIN.</i>

15:16.791 --> 15:19.283
<i>[merry go round music]</i>

15:38.729 --> 15:40.106
MARTIN.

15:53.369 --> 15:55.030
MARTIN!

15:55.121 --> 15:56.953
MARTIN!

16:03.379 --> 16:04.961
<i>MARTIN!</i>

16:05.047 --> 16:06.788
LET ME TALK TO YOU!

16:06.841 --> 16:08.798
LET ME TELL YOU
SOMETHING.

16:08.843 --> 16:11.130
I DON'T WANT
TO HURT YOU, SON.

16:11.220 --> 16:12.836
I WON'T HURT YOU.

16:12.930 --> 16:15.183
<i>(Martin)
I WON'T HURT YOU, SON.</i>

16:17.643 --> 16:19.304
MARTIN!

16:20.980 --> 16:22.812
<i>MARTIN!</i>

16:22.899 --> 16:24.389
MARTIN!

16:24.484 --> 16:26.475
OW! MY LEG!
MY LEG!

16:26.569 --> 16:27.980
MARTIN!

16:59.477 --> 17:01.013
MARTIN.

17:01.103 --> 17:02.844
I ONLY WANTED
TO TELL YOU

17:02.897 --> 17:06.060
THAT THIS IS A WONDERFUL
TIME OF LIFE FOR YOU.

17:06.150 --> 17:10.734
DON'T LET ANY OF IT
GO BY WITHOUT ENJOYING IT.

17:27.421 --> 17:29.708
THERE WON'T BE
ANY MORE MERRY-GO-ROUNDS.

17:29.757 --> 17:32.215
NO MORE COTTON CANDY.

17:32.260 --> 17:35.878
NO MORE BAND CONCERTS.

17:35.972 --> 17:38.885
I ONLY WANTED TO TELL YOU

17:38.933 --> 17:41.641
THAT THIS IS
A WONDERFUL TIME FOR YOU.

17:41.727 --> 17:44.810
NOW. HERE.

17:44.897 --> 17:47.810
THAT'S ALL, MARTIN.

17:47.900 --> 17:50.062
THAT'S ALL
I WANTED TO TELL YOU.

17:50.111 --> 17:51.647
GOD HELP ME.

17:51.737 --> 17:55.196
THAT'S ALL
I WANTED TO TELL YOU.

18:19.557 --> 18:21.013
I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE TO KNOW

18:21.100 --> 18:23.262
<i>THE BOY
WILL BEALL RIGHT.</i>

18:23.311 --> 18:25.302
DOCTOR SAYS HE'LL LIMP SOME,

18:25.396 --> 18:27.683
BUT HE'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

18:27.773 --> 18:29.684
OH, THANK GOD FOR THAT.

18:29.775 --> 18:33.188
YOU DROPPED THIS
AT THE HOUSE.

18:33.279 --> 18:36.442
I LOOKED INSIDE IT.

18:36.490 --> 18:38.777
